        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

    <Paragraph>This Glyph Metrics Viewer sample shows how to use the Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF) GlyphRun object for retrieving the glyph, or character, metrics that describe physical attributes of a single glyph character. You can use this sample to view the glyph metric values of fonts that are installed on your system. The following screenshot shows several glyph metrics displayed for a specified font glyph.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph><Run FontWeight="Bold">Glyph Metrics Viewer</Run>

    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph><Run FontWeight="Bold"/>
      <LineBreak/>
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>For more information on building and running this sample, see Glyph Metrics Viewer Sample.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22">Using the Glyph Metrics Viewer
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>Once the Glyph Metrics Viewer is running, select the font whose glyphs you want to display from the <Run FontWeight="Bold">Font</Run>
 drop-down list box. When you select a font, the application adjusts the <Run FontWeight="Bold">Glyph Index</Run>
 slider control to the maximum number of glyphs defined in the font. Next, select the specific glyph index you want to display, either by moving the position of the slider control or entering the numeric value of the glyph index.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>Select one or more of the <Run FontWeight="Bold">Show Metrics</Run>
 check boxes to display the metrics for the selected glyph. The position of these metrics values correspond to the property values you can retrieve for the glyph using the CharacterMetrics object. The following illustration shows the positions of all the glyph metrics you can display:
    </Paragraph>

